  <summary date="2017-03-08T05:00:00Z" status="Introduced in Senate">Improving Access to Medicare Coverage Act of 2017

This bill amends title XVIII (Medicare) of the Social Security Act to deem an individual receiving outpatient observation services in a hospital to be an inpatient for purposes of satisfying the three-day inpatient hospital-stay requirement&#160;with respect to&#160;Medicare coverage of skilled nursing facility services.</summary>
